Heat the olive oil in a frying pan over a medium heat. Add the garlic and sage and fry for 1-2 minutes, until golden.Add the butternut squash and saut√© for 3-4 minutes, until golden.Add the white wine and cook for one minute.Add the double cream and water, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to simmer for five minutes, until the butternut squash is soft and cooked.Add the pasta, toss together and season, to taste, salt and freshly ground black pepper.Serve in a warm bowl.